  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "23-25. was very sorrowful—Matthew (Mt 19:22) more fully, \"went away sorrowful\"; Mark still more, \"was sad\" or \"sullen\" at that saying, and \"went away grieved.\" Sorry he was, very sorry, to part with Christ; but to part with his riches would have cost him a pang more. When Riches or Heaven, on Christ's terms, were the alternative, the result showed to which side the balance inclined. Thus was he shown to lack the one all-comprehensive requirement of the law—the absolute subjection of the heart to God, and this want vitiated all his other obediences.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
